          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "BRST"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The target assembly was irradiated for 5-7",
                " hours with bremsstrahlung produced by bombarding the",
                " 65-MeV electrons on the 0.1 mm thick tungsten foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A metal of 209Bi target (74.417 g) of 25 cm*2 area",
                " was wrapped with 0.0025 cm thick super pure-aluminum",
                " foil and was fixed on a stand at proper height behind",
                " a 0.1 mm thick tungsten metal foil situated in a",
                " fixed position.",
                "The tungsten metal foil acts as a an electron-",
                " bremsstrahlung converter whereas aluminum foil act as",
                " a recoil catcher of fission product from the bismuth",
                " metal foil during irradiation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma-ray activities of the samples with",
                " fixed geometry were measured one after another by",
                " using an energy and efficiency calibrated HPGe",
                " detector coupled to a PC based 4K-channel analyzer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The post-neutron emission mass yield",
                " distribution and the photo-neutron cross-section of",
                " 209Bi with 65-MeV bremsstrahlung have been determined",
                " using an off-line gamma-ray spectrometric technique."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The photo-peak areas of different gamma-rays of the",
                " nuclides of interest were calculated by subtracting",
                " the linear Compton background from their total net",
                " peak areas.",
                "From the gamma-ray activities of the fission products,",
                " their yields were calculated using decay equation.",
                "Similarly from the gamma-ray activities of the",
                " reaction product, photo-neutron (g,3n) cross-section",
                " was also calculated using similar decay equation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainties shown in the measured",
                " cumulative yields of individual fission products and",
                " photo-neutron cross sections of 209-Bi are the",
                " precision values from two determinations.",
                "The overall uncertainty represents contributions from",
                " both random and systematic errors.",
                "The random error in the observed activity is due to",
                " counting statistics and is estimated to be 10-15%.",
                "The overall systematic error is about 4%.",
                "The total error is around 11-16%.",
                "The systematic errors are due to uncertainties in"
              ]
            },
