          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "It can be seen from Table 2 that the photo-neutron",
                " (G,3N) cross-section of 209-Bi at a 65-MeV",
                "bremsstrahlung energy increases with increasing gamma",
                "ray energy of the 206-Bi up to 803 KeV and then remains",
                "constant above that energy. This is because of the use",
                "of thick bismuth metal foil of 2 mm, which causes",
                "attenuation of the gamma rays of 206-Bi to different",
                "extents depending upon the energy. Above 803 keV, the",
                "attenuation of gamma -rays in a 2-mm thick bismuth foil",
                "is negligible. Photo-neutron (G,3N) cross-section of",
                "1.478(0.054) mb  was obtained after averaging the",
                "experimentally determined value for the gamma energies",
                " of 803 keV and above."
              ]
            }
          ],
